^b@2^*BHoward: ^*N|cp||at|5NT is the correct answer. Partnership might have club slam. Here, because you have so many points, you would like to be in slam, but you are not sure where. So,  you could bid 5N. On good days partner would bid 6 clubs with a club suit. If not, 6N is probably ok. One thing Bergen feels is that suit slams are much easier to play than NT slams. He recommends that often you might even play in a 7 card fit rather than NT. The reason suit slams are often better is you generate extra tricks with ruffs. For example, if you have a 4-4 fit, and can manage 2 ruffs in one hand, you take six trump tricks instead of just 4 tricks in the suit.|
